JOHANNESBURG - The R24 freeway in Ekurhuleni has been reopened following traffic chaos on Tuesday morning, as the westbound section near Van Riebeeck Road leading towards Gillooly`s interchange was closed. A truck crashed into a concrete barrier and caught fire on Monday night. JHB - R24 West, #TruckFire (Update), Road RE-OPENED on the link to the N12 West (towards Gilloolys) pic.twitter.com/mcYepYPHTV Ekurhuleni Disaster and Emergency Management Services said the road was closed because the slippery surface had to be decontaminated while the wreckage was removed. - Additional reporting by African News Agency eNCA